<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Data CreatedBy="admin" CreatedOn="634110031183587346" UpdatedBy="admin" UpdatedOn="634292193212631608">
  <Properties />
  <Nodes>
    <Header Code="HeaderElement1" Type="Subtitle" ShowInTOC="0"><![CDATA[The example]]></Header>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement1"><![CDATA[<p>Select item in <em>ComboBox </em>and text and image alignment and relation between them&nbsp;will be&nbsp;changed respectively.</p>]]></Paragraph>
    <Header Code="HeaderElement2" Type="Subtitle" ShowInTOC="0"><![CDATA[General Info]]></Header>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement2"><![CDATA[<p>The Visual WebGui <em>Button </em>contains the <em>TextImageRelation</em>, <em>ImageAlign </em>and <em>TextAlign </em>property for manipulating with image-text alignment and relations. <br /><br />The <em>TextImageRelation </em>property defines the position of text and image relative to each other. <br />The property&nbsp;values could be:<br /><strong>Overlay </strong>- specifies that the image and text share the same space on a control;<br /><strong>ImageAboveText </strong>- specifies that the image is displayed vertically above the text of a control;<br /><strong>TextAboveImage </strong>- specifies that the text is displayed vertically above the image of a control;<br /><strong>ImageBeforeText </strong>- specifies that the image is displayed horizontally before the text of a control;<br /><strong>TextBeforeImage </strong>- specifies that the text is displayed horizontally before the image of a control.<br /><br />The <em>ImageAlign </em>defines the image alignment on the button. <br />The <em>TextAlign </em>defines the text alignment on the button.<br />The property values could be:<br /><strong>TopLeft </strong>&ndash; text/image is vertically aligned at the top, and horizontally aligned on the left;<br /><strong>TopCenter </strong>- text/image is vertically aligned at the top, and horizontally aligned at the center;<br /><strong>TopRight </strong>- text/image is vertically aligned at the top, and horizontally aligned on the right;<br /><strong>MiddleLeft </strong>- text/image is vertically aligned in the middle, and horizontally aligned on the left;<br /><strong>MiddleCenter </strong>- text/image is vertically aligned in the middle, and horizontally aligned at the center;<br /><strong>MiddleRight </strong>- text/image is vertically aligned in the middle, and horizontally aligned on the right;<br /><strong>BottomLeft </strong>- text/image is vertically aligned at the bottom, and horizontally aligned on the left;<br /><strong>BottomCenter </strong>- text/image is vertically aligned at the bottom, and horizontally aligned at the center;<br /><strong>BottomRight </strong>- text/image is vertically aligned at the bottom, and horizontally aligned on the right.</p>]]></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement3" />
  </Nodes>
</Data>